1
00:04:18,937 --> 00:04:21,624
Who's that stumbling around in the dark?

2
00:04:22,138 --> 00:04:25,580
State your business
or prepare to get winged!

3
00:04:26,309 --> 00:04:28,787
Calm yourselves, gentlemen.

4
00:04:28,853 --> 00:04:30,530
I mean you no harm.

5
00:04:31,356 --> 00:04:34,362
I'm simply a fellow weary traveler.

6
00:04:34,707 --> 00:04:35,889
Oh boy.

7
00:04:37,678 --> 00:04:39,416
Good cold evening, gentlemen.

8
00:04:39,457 --> 00:04:41,969
I'm looking for a pair of slave traders

9
00:04:41,971 --> 00:04:43,846
that go by the name of the Speck Brothers.

10
00:04:43,989 --> 00:04:45,074
Might that be you?

11
00:04:46,913 --> 00:04:47,999
Who wants to know?

12
00:04:48,208 --> 00:04:49,341
Well, I do.

13
00:04:49,832 --> 00:04:51,980
I'm Dr. King Schultz.
This is my horse, Fritz.

14
00:04:53,684 --> 00:04:54,907
What kinda doctor?

15
00:04:55,671 --> 00:04:56,597
Dentist.

16
00:04:57,132 --> 00:04:58,540
Now, are you the Speck Brothers?

17
00:04:58,591 --> 00:05:00,133
And did you purchase those men

18
00:05:00,157 --> 00:05:01,515
at the Greenville slave auction?

19
00:05:01,552 --> 00:05:02,353
So what?

20
00:05:02,354 --> 00:05:04,471
So I wish to parley with you.

21
00:05:04,542 --> 00:05:05,541
Speak English.

22
00:05:06,214 --> 00:05:07,257
Oh sorry.

23
00:05:07,809 --> 00:05:10,019
Please forgive me.
It is a second language.

24
00:05:10,186 --> 00:05:13,760
Now, amongst your inventory,
I've been led to believe,

25
00:05:13,838 --> 00:05:15,914
is a specimen I'm keen to acquire.

26
00:05:16,437 --> 00:05:17,897
Hello, you poor devils!

27
00:05:19,028 --> 00:05:22,037
Is there one amongst you
who was formerly a resident

28
00:05:22,039 --> 00:05:24,565
of the Carrucan plantation?

29
00:05:26,014 --> 00:05:27,799
I'm from the Carrucan plantation.

30
00:05:29,924 --> 00:05:30,803
Who said that?

31
00:06:18,254 --> 00:06:19,369
What's your name?

32
00:06:23,801 --> 00:06:24,853
Django.

33
00:06:26,178 --> 00:06:28,335
Then you are exactly the one
I'm looking for.

34
00:06:30,475 --> 00:06:32,195
Do you know
who the Brittle Brothers are?

35
00:06:36,665 --> 00:06:37,666
Who are they?

36
00:06:39,882 --> 00:06:40,828
Big John.

37
00:06:42,153 --> 00:06:42,993
Ellis.

38
00:06:44,906 --> 00:06:45,685
Roger.

39
00:06:46,097 --> 00:06:47,165
Sometime they call him...

40
00:06:47,572 --> 00:06:48,623
Lil Raj.

41
00:06:50,203 --> 00:06:52,328
They was overseers
at the Carrucan plantation.

42
00:06:52,580 --> 00:06:53,664
Not anymore.

43
00:06:56,837 --> 00:06:57,794
Tell me...

44
00:06:58,482 --> 00:07:01,454
if you were to see any of these
three gentlemen again,

45
00:07:01,456 --> 00:07:03,092
would you recognize them?
Hey.

46
00:07:04,284 --> 00:07:05,665
Stop talking to him like that.

47
00:07:05,864 --> 00:07:06,714
Like What?

48
00:07:07,296 --> 00:07:08,245
Like that.

49
00:07:08,568 --> 00:07:11,216
My good man,
I'm simply trying to ascertain...

50
00:07:11,218 --> 00:07:12,394
Speak English, goddamn it.

51
00:07:13,230 --> 00:07:15,216
Everybody calm down.

52
00:07:15,276 --> 00:07:16,966
I'm simply a customer,

53
00:07:16,967 --> 00:07:19,310
trying to conduct a transaction.

54
00:07:19,357 --> 00:07:20,219
I don't care.

55
00:07:20,487 --> 00:07:21,984
No sale. Now, off with you.

56
00:07:22,966 --> 00:07:25,154
Don't be ridiculous.
Of course they're for sale.

57
00:07:25,879 --> 00:07:26,920
Move it.

58
00:07:27,805 --> 00:07:28,919
My good man,

59
00:07:29,154 --> 00:07:32,661
did you simply get carried
away with your dramatic gesture

60
00:07:32,663 --> 00:07:36,056
or are you pointing your weapon at me
with lethal intention?

61
00:07:37,856 --> 00:07:39,431
Last chance, fancy pants.

62
00:07:40,878 --> 00:07:42,504
Oh, very well.

63
00:08:12,340 --> 00:08:14,759
I'm sorry to put a bullet in your beast,

64
00:08:14,793 --> 00:08:16,844
but I didn't want you to do anything rash

65
00:08:16,846 --> 00:08:18,958
before you had a moment
to come to your senses.

66
00:08:19,743 --> 00:08:22,430
You goddamn son of a bitch!

67
00:08:22,984 --> 00:08:25,089
You shot Roscoe!
Well...

68
00:08:25,673 --> 00:08:27,161
And you killed Ace!

69
00:08:27,550 --> 00:08:30,305
I only shot your brother once
he threatened to shoot me.

70
00:08:30,601 --> 00:08:33,222
And I do believe I have...
one, two, three, four...

71
00:08:33,529 --> 00:08:35,141
five witnesses,

72
00:08:35,142 --> 00:08:36,350
who can attest to that fact.

73
00:08:36,702 --> 00:08:38,357
Damn leg's busted!

74
00:08:38,444 --> 00:08:39,481
No doubt.

75
00:08:39,671 --> 00:08:42,597
Now, if you could keep your
caterwauling down to a minimum,

76
00:08:42,599 --> 00:08:45,405
I'd like to finish my line
of inquiry with young Django.

77
00:08:49,614 --> 00:08:51,689
God-fucking-damn it!

78
00:08:51,691 --> 00:08:52,662
As I was saying...

79
00:08:53,413 --> 00:08:55,661
if you were to see the Brittle Brothers,

80
00:08:55,662 --> 00:08:57,125
again you could recognize them?

81
00:08:57,622 --> 00:08:58,489
Yeah.

82
00:08:59,631 --> 00:09:00,924
Sold American!

83
00:09:00,958 --> 00:09:02,177
So, Mr. Speck?

84
00:09:02,178 --> 00:09:04,579
Mr. Speck?
How much for young Django here?

85
00:09:10,366 --> 00:09:12,595
That iron is nasty business.

86
00:09:18,222 --> 00:09:19,910
Oh, could you hold this for a moment?

87
00:09:22,313 --> 00:09:23,347
Thank you.

88
00:09:23,348 --> 00:09:24,121
Django?

89
00:09:24,277 --> 00:09:25,579
Get up on that horse.

90
00:09:26,278 --> 00:09:27,734
Also, if I were you,

91
00:09:28,086 --> 00:09:31,896
I'd take that winter coat
the dear departed Speck left behind.

92
00:09:46,128 --> 00:09:46,973
Nigger!

93
00:09:47,197 --> 00:09:49,683
Don't you touch my brother's coat.

94
00:10:01,539 --> 00:10:03,035
Goddamn it!

95
00:10:07,772 --> 00:10:09,098
One hundred...

96
00:10:09,651 --> 00:10:10,593
ten...

97
00:10:11,294 --> 00:10:12,320
20...

98
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:14,448
and five...

99
00:10:15,935 --> 00:10:17,102
for young Django here.

100
00:10:17,233 --> 00:10:19,647
And since he won't be needing it anymore,

101
00:10:19,649 --> 00:10:21,835
I'd like to purchase your brother's nag.

102
00:10:22,698 --> 00:10:23,720
Also,

103
00:10:23,926 --> 00:10:25,002
Mr. Speck,

104
00:10:25,003 --> 00:10:27,545
I'm afraid I will require a bill of sale.

105
00:10:27,712 --> 00:10:28,635
Do you have one?

106
00:10:29,858 --> 00:10:31,860
You go to hell, dentist.

107
00:10:32,968 --> 00:10:33,952
I thought not.

108
00:10:34,930 --> 00:10:35,925
No worries.

109
00:10:36,678 --> 00:10:37,886
I come prepared.

110
00:10:42,482 --> 00:10:43,416
Thank you.

111
00:10:44,429 --> 00:10:46,308
This will serve nicely,

112
00:10:46,309 --> 00:10:47,779
as a bill of sale.

113
00:11:05,609 --> 00:11:08,434
Now, as to you poor devils.

114
00:11:09,567 --> 00:11:10,850
So, as I see it,

115
00:11:11,641 --> 00:11:14,033
when it comes to the subject
of what to do next,

116
00:11:14,423 --> 00:11:15,908
you gentlemen have...

117
00:11:15,909 --> 00:11:17,038
two choices.

118
00:11:17,507 --> 00:11:18,082
One.

119
00:11:18,730 --> 00:11:19,808
Once I'm gone,

120
00:11:20,238 --> 00:11:22,786
you could lift that beast
off the remaining Speck,

121
00:11:22,788 --> 00:11:24,477
then carry him to the nearest town.

122
00:11:24,747 --> 00:11:27,937
Which would be at least
37 miles back the way you came.

123
00:11:28,535 --> 00:11:29,340
Or two.

124
00:11:30,699 --> 00:11:32,327
You could unshackle yourselves,

125
00:11:32,998 --> 00:11:34,070
take that rifle,

126
00:11:34,394 --> 00:11:35,572
put a bullet in his head,

127
00:11:35,768 --> 00:11:37,090
bury the two of them deep,

128
00:11:37,262 --> 00:11:40,493
and then make your way to a more
enlightened area of this country.

129
00:11:41,694 --> 00:11:42,709
Choice is yours.

130
00:11:43,591 --> 00:11:47,474
And on the off chance there are
any astronomy aficionados amongst you,

131
00:11:47,528 --> 00:11:49,973
the North Star is that one.

132
00:11:52,055 --> 00:11:52,883
Tada.

133
00:12:10,044 --> 00:12:11,476
Now wait a minute, fellas.

134
00:12:11,645 --> 00:12:13,305
Let's talk about this!

135
00:12:17,613 --> 00:12:20,907
You got to be reasonable
in a situation like this!

136
00:12:22,493 --> 00:12:25,496
I'm not a bad guy.
I'm just doing my job!

137
00:12:25,663 --> 00:12:26,618
Blueberry,

138
00:12:27,132 --> 00:12:29,104
didn't I give you my last apple?

139
00:12:29,660 --> 00:12:30,699
Tell you what, boys.

140
00:12:30,916 --> 00:12:32,533
Take me to the doc in El Paso,

141
00:12:32,877 --> 00:12:34,263
I'll get you your freedom.

142
00:12:34,903 --> 00:12:36,357
No. No, please...

143
00:13:23,846 --> 00:13:25,222
Alright, now.

144
00:13:25,389 --> 00:13:27,642
I'd like you to take two of these tonight,

145
00:13:28,159 --> 00:13:29,485
and then in the morning...

146
00:13:32,208 --> 00:13:33,558
That's a nigger on a horse.

147
00:13:59,518 --> 00:14:00,935
What's everybody staring at?

148
00:14:01,461 --> 00:14:03,481
They ain't never seen
no nigger on a horse before.

149
00:14:27,117 --> 00:14:28,861
Good morning, innkeeper!

150
00:14:30,698 --> 00:14:32,776
Two beers for two weary travelers.

151
00:14:32,944 --> 00:14:34,833
It's still a bit early.

152
00:14:35,191 --> 00:14:37,141
We won't be open for another hour.

153
00:14:37,797 --> 00:14:39,494
By then, we'll be serving breakfast.

154
00:14:42,646 --> 00:14:44,906
What the hell you think you're doing, boy?

155
00:14:45,177 --> 00:14:46,786
Get that nigger outta here!

156
00:14:52,270 --> 00:14:54,075
Help! Help!

157
00:14:54,140 --> 00:14:55,131
Innkeeper!

158
00:14:55,490 --> 00:14:56,383
Remember,

159
00:14:56,384 --> 00:14:58,350
get the sheriff, not the marshal.

160
00:14:58,710 --> 00:15:00,357
Sheriff! Help!

161
00:15:00,835 --> 00:15:01,681
Alas.

162
00:15:03,362 --> 00:15:05,906
Now we must act as our own bartender.

163
00:15:08,325 --> 00:15:09,873
Sit down, my boy.

164
00:15:20,019 --> 00:15:21,348
What kind of dentist are you?

165
00:15:23,465 --> 00:15:28,053
Despite that cart, I haven't
practiced dentistry in five years.

166
00:15:32,987 --> 00:15:35,192
But these days,
I practice a new profession...

167
00:15:38,461 --> 00:15:39,503
bounty hunter.

168
00:15:46,374 --> 00:15:47,882
Do you know what a bounty hunter is?

169
00:15:48,699 --> 00:15:49,413
No.

170
00:15:49,767 --> 00:15:50,602
Well...

171
00:15:52,745 --> 00:15:56,874
the way the slave trade
deals in human lives for cash,

172
00:15:57,041 --> 00:15:59,223
a bounty hunter deals in corpses.

173
00:16:00,713 --> 00:16:01,246
Hat.

174
00:16:05,507 --> 00:16:06,372
Prost.

175
00:16:15,428 --> 00:16:18,104
The state places a bounty
on a man's head.

176
00:16:18,187 --> 00:16:21,184
I track that man, I find that man,
I kill that man.

177
00:16:21,186 --> 00:16:25,190
After I've killed him, I transport that
man's corpse back to the authorities.

178
00:16:25,575 --> 00:16:27,700
Sometimes that's easier said than done.

179
00:16:27,905 --> 00:16:30,089
I show that corpse
to the authorities,

180
00:16:30,090 --> 00:16:32,576
proving yes, indeed,
I truly have killed him,

181
00:16:32,743 --> 00:16:35,197
at which point the authorities
pay me the bounty.

182
00:16:35,913 --> 00:16:36,465
So,

183
00:16:36,926 --> 00:16:39,573
like slavery,
it's a flesh for cash business.

184
00:16:40,876 --> 00:16:41,924
What's a bounty?

185
00:16:45,673 --> 00:16:47,132
It's like a reward.

186
00:16:47,798 --> 00:16:48,904
You kill people?

187
00:16:49,261 --> 00:16:50,399
And they give you a reward?

188
00:16:51,399 --> 00:16:52,721
Certain people, yeah.

189
00:16:53,106 --> 00:16:54,058
Bad people?

190
00:16:55,530 --> 00:16:57,306
Badder they are, bigger the reward.

191
00:16:58,443 --> 00:16:59,777
Which brings me to you.

192
00:17:00,771 --> 00:17:03,993
And I must admit, I'm at a bit of
a quandary when it comes to you.

193
00:17:05,431 --> 00:17:07,611
On one hand, I despise slavery.

194
00:17:07,937 --> 00:17:09,297
On the other hand,

195
00:17:10,177 --> 00:17:11,219
I need your help.

196
00:17:11,221 --> 00:17:13,771
If you're not in a position to refuse,
all the better.

197
00:17:15,425 --> 00:17:16,644
So, for the time being,

198
00:17:16,645 --> 00:17:19,522
I'm gonna make this slavery
malarkey work to my benefit.

199
00:17:20,541 --> 00:17:21,324
Still,

200
00:17:21,810 --> 00:17:22,844
having said that,

201
00:17:24,111 --> 00:17:25,118
I feel guilty.

202
00:17:26,944 --> 00:17:27,740
So,

203
00:17:28,766 --> 00:17:32,136
I would like the two of us
to enter into an agreement.

204
00:17:39,371 --> 00:17:40,964
I'm looking for the Brittle Brothers.

205
00:17:45,785 --> 00:17:47,422
However, at this endeavor,

206
00:17:47,496 --> 00:17:49,295
I'm at a slight disadvantage,

207
00:17:49,829 --> 00:17:51,877
insofar as I don't know
what they look like.

208
00:17:53,900 --> 00:17:54,902
But you do.

209
00:17:55,730 --> 00:17:56,452
Don't ya?

210
00:17:57,019 --> 00:17:58,617
I know what they look like alright.

211
00:17:59,188 --> 00:17:59,853
Good.

212
00:18:00,525 --> 00:18:01,982
So here's my agreement.

213
00:18:02,868 --> 00:18:05,673
You travel with me until we find them.
Where we going?

214
00:18:06,323 --> 00:18:09,139
I hear at least two of them
are overseeing up in Gatlinburg,

215
00:18:09,148 --> 00:18:10,423
but I don't know where.

216
00:18:11,468 --> 00:18:14,059
That means we visit every plantation

217
00:18:14,060 --> 00:18:15,764
in Gatlinburg till we find them.

218
00:18:15,846 --> 00:18:17,314
And when we find them,

219
00:18:18,338 --> 00:18:19,609
you point them out,

220
00:18:19,610 --> 00:18:20,732
and I kill them.

221
00:18:22,258 --> 00:18:23,300
You do that,

222
00:18:24,108 --> 00:18:25,776
I agree to give you your freedom,

223
00:18:25,854 --> 00:18:28,365
$25 per Brittle Brother.

224
00:18:28,366 --> 00:18:29,678
That's $75.

225
00:18:30,171 --> 00:18:32,242
And as if on cue,

226
00:18:32,243 --> 00:18:33,697
here comes the sheriff.

227
00:18:41,455 --> 00:18:43,090
Ok, boys.

228
00:18:43,394 --> 00:18:44,484
Fun's over.

229
00:18:45,862 --> 00:18:46,838
Come on out.

230
00:18:50,509 --> 00:18:52,066
Alright folks,

231
00:18:52,815 --> 00:18:54,176
calm down.

232
00:18:55,219 --> 00:18:56,670
Go about your business.

233
00:18:58,123 --> 00:18:59,998
These jokers will be gone soon.

234
00:19:02,167 --> 00:19:02,987
Now,

235
00:19:03,557 --> 00:19:06,675
why you all wanna come
into my town and start trouble?

236
00:19:08,820 --> 00:19:10,768
Scare all these nice people.

237
00:19:12,248 --> 00:19:14,493
You ain't got nothing better to do,

238
00:19:15,184 --> 00:19:18,282
than to come into Bill Sharp's town

239
00:19:18,422 --> 00:19:20,684
and show your ass?

240
00:19:29,366 --> 00:19:31,098
What'd you just do to our sheriff?

241
00:19:44,234 --> 00:19:45,910
Now you can get the marshal.

242
00:19:48,083 --> 00:19:49,227
Marshal!

243
00:19:49,313 --> 00:19:50,261
Marshal!

244
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:51,648
Should we wait inside?

245
00:19:51,754 --> 00:19:52,751
Can we just leave?

246
00:19:52,860 --> 00:19:53,707
After you.

247
00:19:56,652 --> 00:20:00,168
Move that buckboard a long ways
across the street from the saloon.

248
00:20:00,909 --> 00:20:03,236
I want six men, six rifles behind it.

249
00:20:04,085 --> 00:20:06,326
I want two men,
two rifles up on this roof.

250
00:20:06,446 --> 00:20:08,114
Two men, two rifles on that roof.

251
00:20:08,792 --> 00:20:10,976
All the barrels aimed at that front door.

252
00:20:12,225 --> 00:20:14,753
Somebody get poor Bill
outta the goddamn street.

253
00:20:16,091 --> 00:20:17,223
You in the saloon!

254
00:20:18,692 --> 00:20:21,528
We got a hundred rifles aimed
at every way out of that building.

255
00:20:22,565 --> 00:20:25,029
You got one chance
to get out of this alive.

256
00:20:26,476 --> 00:20:29,164
You and your nigger come out right now
with your hands over your head,

257
00:20:29,173 --> 00:20:30,658
and I mean right now.

258
00:20:32,232 --> 00:20:35,652
Is this the marshal I have
the pleasure of addressing?

259
00:20:36,253 --> 00:20:37,230
Yes, it is.

260
00:20:37,993 --> 00:20:39,865
This is U.S. Marshal Gill Tatum.

261
00:20:40,274 --> 00:20:42,023
Na wunderbar, marshal.

262
00:20:42,826 --> 00:20:46,413
I have relieved myself of all weapons,

263
00:20:46,979 --> 00:20:49,554
and just as you have instructed,

264
00:20:49,789 --> 00:20:52,336
I am ready to step outside

265
00:20:52,718 --> 00:20:54,162
with my hands,

266
00:20:54,163 --> 00:20:56,362
raised above my head.

267
00:20:57,949 --> 00:21:00,359
I trust as a representative

268
00:21:00,361 --> 00:21:03,897
of the criminal justice system
of the United States of America,

269
00:21:04,025 --> 00:21:05,911
I shan't be shot down

270
00:21:06,060 --> 00:21:09,809
in the street by either
you or your deputies

271
00:21:10,005 --> 00:21:12,648
before I've had my day in court.

272
00:21:13,119 --> 00:21:14,680
You mean like you did our sheriff.

273
00:21:15,317 --> 00:21:17,110
Shot him down like a dog in the street.

274
00:21:17,277 --> 00:21:19,613
Yes, that's exactly what I mean.

