00:54:49,855 --> 00:54:52,800
This corpse is worth $7,000.

814
00:54:53,667 --> 00:54:55,766
Now quit your pussyfooting
and shoot him.

815
00:55:06,012 --> 00:55:06,762
Pa?

816
00:55:07,648 --> 00:55:08,424
Pa!

817
00:55:17,357 --> 00:55:18,331
Here.

818
00:55:19,234 --> 00:55:21,319
You need to keep
this Smitty Bacall handbill.

819
00:55:21,486 --> 00:55:22,061
Why?

820
00:55:22,357 --> 00:55:23,388
It's good luck.

821
00:55:23,738 --> 00:55:26,024
You always keep the handbill
of your first bounty.

822
00:56:14,456 --> 00:56:16,006
That's accurate.

823
00:57:24,192 --> 00:57:25,761
Doctor, Django,

824
00:57:25,763 --> 00:57:26,994
how the hell are you?

825
00:57:28,556 --> 00:57:30,095
Who the hell-a you got there?

826
00:57:30,863 --> 00:57:32,453
The Wilson-Lowe Gang.

827
00:57:33,085 --> 00:57:35,701
Who the hell is the Wilson-Lowe Gang?

828
00:57:36,762 --> 00:57:39,472
Bad Chuck Wilson
and meaner Bobby Lowe

829
00:57:39,773 --> 00:57:41,044
and three of their acolytes.

830
00:57:42,808 --> 00:57:45,089
Well, just leave them out here,
they ain't going nowhere.

831
00:57:45,308 --> 00:57:47,524
Why don't you come in then
out of the snowy snow

832
00:57:47,723 --> 00:57:49,021
and get yourselves some coffee.

833
00:57:49,592 --> 00:57:52,137
We had a birthday yesterday.
Got some cake.

834
00:57:52,591 --> 00:57:53,636
Pretty good.

835
00:58:27,172 --> 00:58:28,423
Keep moving.

836
00:58:28,590 --> 00:58:30,550
Get on up on that auction block.

837
00:58:32,093 --> 00:58:34,470
Don't let that mud slow you down.
Keep going.

838
00:58:50,904 --> 00:58:52,155
Keep going!

839
00:58:54,616 --> 00:58:56,418
Broomhilda Von Shaft.

840
00:58:56,662 --> 00:58:57,927
Age 27.

841
00:58:58,703 --> 00:59:00,121
'R' on right cheek.

842
00:59:01,927 --> 00:59:04,042
Calvin Candie.

843
00:59:04,302 --> 00:59:07,565
He owns the fourth biggest
cotton plantation in Mississippi.

844
00:59:07,566 --> 00:59:08,723
Candyland.

845
00:59:09,015 --> 00:59:09,980
Candyland?

846
00:59:10,518 --> 00:59:11,602
Oh, so you've heard of it.

847
00:59:11,642 --> 00:59:13,316
Ain't no slave ain't heard of Candyland.

848
00:59:13,801 --> 00:59:16,163
Well apparently,
that's where your wife is...

849
00:59:16,638 --> 00:59:19,182
and that's the repellant gentleman
who owns her.

850
00:59:19,613 --> 00:59:22,043
Let's just hope she works in
the house, not in the field.

851
00:59:22,294 --> 00:59:23,663
Oh, no, she ain't no field nigger.

852
00:59:24,479 --> 00:59:26,175
She... She pretty.

853
00:59:27,335 --> 00:59:28,787
And she talk good, too.

854
00:59:30,652 --> 00:59:32,493
But when they tore her back up
and then they...

855
00:59:33,834 --> 00:59:35,439
burned that runaway r on her cheek...

856
00:59:37,242 --> 00:59:38,409
they goddamned her.

857
00:59:43,122 --> 00:59:44,828
She ain't no field nigger
but she ain't good enough

858
00:59:44,830 --> 00:59:46,016
for the house no more either.

859
00:59:46,834 --> 00:59:48,399
They gonna try to make her a comfort girl.

860
00:59:48,497 --> 00:59:49,469
What's a comfort?

861
00:59:51,089 --> 00:59:52,516
Not while I got freedom.

862
00:59:53,967 --> 00:59:55,440
Not while I got my gun.

863
00:59:58,846 --> 01:00:00,360
So do we offer to buy her?

864
01:00:03,340 --> 01:00:04,334
So...

865
01:00:06,339 --> 01:00:07,224
say...

866
01:00:09,983 --> 01:00:10,990
a man,

867
01:00:11,271 --> 01:00:12,680
wants to buy a horse.

868
01:00:13,243 --> 01:00:14,884
Needs to buy a horse.

869
01:00:16,529 --> 01:00:18,094
He walks up to the farmer's farm,

870
01:00:18,110 --> 01:00:19,490
and he knocks on the farmer's door

871
01:00:19,492 --> 01:00:21,395
and asks the farmer to buy his horse.

872
01:00:21,397 --> 01:00:23,191
And do you know what the farmer says?

873
01:00:23,288 --> 01:00:25,239
The farmer says, no.

874
01:00:27,115 --> 01:00:29,354
Well, I say fuck that farmer,

875
01:00:29,986 --> 01:00:31,358
and I'm stealing that horse.

876
01:00:32,130 --> 01:00:34,744
Fair enough.
But now you're a horse thief,

877
01:00:34,745 --> 01:00:36,385
and they hang horse thieves.

878
01:00:36,591 --> 01:00:38,852
Not to mention the horse goes back
to its original owner,

879
01:00:38,854 --> 01:00:40,511
because the horse is still his property.

880
01:00:40,778 --> 01:00:41,867
We need her,

881
01:00:42,235 --> 01:00:43,073
and...

882
01:00:43,321 --> 01:00:44,407
we need a bill of sale.

883
01:00:44,559 --> 01:00:46,512
Well, if we ain't gonna try to buy her,
then how we gonna get her?

884
01:00:48,183 --> 01:00:51,609
May I offer an alternative plan of action?

885
01:00:51,777 --> 01:00:52,872
Go ahead.

886
01:00:53,659 --> 01:00:54,202
So...

887
01:00:55,455 --> 01:00:56,484
the man,

888
01:00:56,784 --> 01:00:58,185
walks up to the farmer's farm,

889
01:00:58,235 --> 01:00:59,778
he knocks on the farmer's door...

890
01:01:00,540 --> 01:01:02,065
and asks,

891
01:01:02,066 --> 01:01:03,592
not to buy the horse,

892
01:01:04,112 --> 01:01:05,536
but the farm.

893
01:01:05,538 --> 01:01:09,334
And makes an offer so ridiculous,

894
01:01:09,481 --> 01:01:12,025
the farmer is forced to say yes.

895
01:01:12,878 --> 01:01:14,675
We gonna offer to buy Candyland?

896
01:01:14,676 --> 01:01:15,822
No, it's far too big.

897
01:01:15,907 --> 01:01:18,715
But apparently this farmer
ain't all about the farm.

898
01:01:20,667 --> 01:01:22,711
How much do you know
about Mandingo fighting?

899
01:01:22,753 --> 01:01:23,427
What?

900
01:01:23,835 --> 01:01:26,914
Can you convincingly
masquerade as someone

901
01:01:26,916 --> 01:01:28,809
who is an expert on Mandingo fighting?

902
01:01:28,840 --> 01:01:29,548
Why?

903
01:01:30,204 --> 01:01:31,641
Because my character

904
01:01:31,642 --> 01:01:34,006
is that of a big money buyer
from Dusseldorf,

905
01:01:34,009 --> 01:01:35,851
here in Greenville to buy my way

906
01:01:35,887 --> 01:01:37,273
into the Mandingo fight game.

907
01:01:37,430 --> 01:01:38,914
And your character

908
01:01:38,953 --> 01:01:41,361
is a Mandingo expert
I hired to help me do it.

909
01:01:41,445 --> 01:01:42,995
They call that One-Eyed Charley.

910
01:01:46,597 --> 01:01:47,713
Bonjour.
<font color="#00ffff"><i>Good morning</i></font>

911
01:01:48,157 --> 01:01:49,174
Bonsoir, <font color="#00ffff"><i>Good evening,</i></font>

912
01:01:49,175 --> 01:01:51,116
ma petite femme noire.
<font color="#00ffff"><i>my little black woman.</i></font>

913
01:01:51,263 --> 01:01:53,715
We're here to see Mr. Calvin Candie.

914
01:01:54,109 --> 01:01:55,528
Entraz.

915
01:01:58,049 --> 01:01:59,509
Thank you.

916
01:02:00,551 --> 01:02:02,462
You want me to play a black slaver?

917
01:02:03,570 --> 01:02:05,357
Ain't nothing lower than a black slaver.

918
01:02:06,337 --> 01:02:09,252
A black slaver is lower
than the head house nigger...

919
01:02:10,443 --> 01:02:12,146
and buddy, that's pretty fucking low.

920
01:02:13,791 --> 01:02:15,675
Then play him that way.

921
01:02:15,733 --> 01:02:17,574
Give me your...

922
01:02:17,887 --> 01:02:19,730
black slaver.

923
01:02:22,448 --> 01:02:25,892
♪ <i>Along came the 219. Toot! Toot!</i> ♪

924
01:02:25,893 --> 01:02:27,412
♪ <i>Peanut butter!</i> ♪

925
01:02:31,165 --> 01:02:32,881
Dr. Schultz!

926
01:02:33,209 --> 01:02:34,856
Good to see you again!

927
01:02:34,857 --> 01:02:36,421
Mr. Moguy.

928
01:02:36,519 --> 01:02:39,653
Thank you for your assistance
in creating the opportunity

929
01:02:39,690 --> 01:02:41,989
for this appointment.
Nonsense, it's my job.

930
01:02:42,611 --> 01:02:45,558
So this is the One-Eyed Charley
I've heard so much about.

931
01:02:45,560 --> 01:02:47,858
Yes, this is Django Freeman.

932
01:02:48,245 --> 01:02:50,902
Django, this is Mr. Candie's lawyer,
Leonide Moguy.

933
01:02:51,088 --> 01:02:52,638
Just call me Leo.

934
01:02:53,062 --> 01:02:56,113
Calvin's in the Julius Caesar room.
You all wanna follow me?

935
01:02:56,704 --> 01:02:58,998
How long have you been
associated with Mr. Candie?

936
01:02:59,612 --> 01:03:01,168
Calvin's father
and I were about...

937
01:03:01,194 --> 01:03:03,157
11 when we went
to boarding school together.

938
01:03:03,575 --> 01:03:06,468
Calvin's father's father
put me through law school.

939
01:03:06,701 --> 01:03:09,704
One could almost say
I was raised to be Calvin's lawyer.

940
01:03:09,871 --> 01:03:11,471
One could almost say youse a nigger.

941
01:03:12,631 --> 01:03:13,601
What did you say?

942
01:03:14,286 --> 01:03:17,039
I said...
Nothing, he's just being cheeky.

943
01:03:17,543 --> 01:03:21,964
Anything else about Mr. Candie
that I should know before I meet him?

944
01:03:21,966 --> 01:03:24,239
Yes, he is a bit of a Francophile.

945
01:03:24,553 --> 01:03:26,044
What civilized people aren't?

946
01:03:26,095 --> 01:03:28,600
And he prefers Monsieur Candie
to Mr. Candie.

947
01:03:28,603 --> 01:03:30,751
Si c'est cela qu'il prefere.
<font color="#00ffff"><i>Whatever he prefers.</i></font>

948
01:03:30,771 --> 01:03:32,323
He doesn't speak French.

949
01:03:32,351 --> 01:03:34,705
Don't speak French to him,
it'll embarrass him.

950
01:03:38,065 --> 01:03:40,318
Get back on top, now!
Turn around!

951
01:03:40,485 --> 01:03:41,779
There you go.

952
01:03:42,356 --> 01:03:43,456
There you go.

953
01:03:45,734 --> 01:03:48,123
Why do you want to get in
the Mandingo business?

954
01:03:50,745 --> 01:03:54,252
You don't intend to allow your second
to make the proper introductions?

955
01:03:55,497 --> 01:03:56,699
Quit stalling, now.

956
01:03:57,461 --> 01:03:58,628
Answer the question.

957
01:04:01,297 --> 01:04:02,370
The awful truth?

958
01:04:03,278 --> 01:04:04,357
I'm bored.

959
01:04:04,991 --> 01:04:06,679
This seems like a good bit of fun.

960
01:04:12,183 --> 01:04:14,185
Well, come on over.

961
01:04:14,352 --> 01:04:17,063
We got us a fight going on
that's a good bit of fun.

962
01:04:21,108 --> 01:04:22,865
Won't you accompany me to the bar?

963
01:04:31,577 --> 01:04:33,360
You don't wear a hat in the house,
white man.

964
01:04:33,362 --> 01:04:34,344
Even I know that.

965
01:04:43,235 --> 01:04:45,038
Dr. Schultz.
What a rare pleasure.

966
01:04:45,040 --> 01:04:46,173
Keep fighting, niggers.

967
01:04:46,789 --> 01:04:48,239
And I might add, an honor.

968
01:04:48,724 --> 01:04:49,707
Honor to meet you.

969
01:04:49,709 --> 01:04:51,760
Please have a seat,
the pleasure's all mine.

970
01:04:51,762 --> 01:04:54,323
Get free man Django here
whatever he wants.

971
01:04:55,268 --> 01:04:57,365
And I'll have sweet tea and bourbon.

972
01:05:17,206 --> 01:05:18,969
Use your weight boy, use your weight!

973
01:05:18,970 --> 01:05:20,081
There you go.

974
01:05:20,683 --> 01:05:22,529
He's much bigger and stronger!

975
01:05:23,151 --> 01:05:24,182
Come on, now!

976
01:05:24,589 --> 01:05:27,446
He's not doing what I told him,
for God's sakes.

977
01:05:28,200 --> 01:05:29,488
Bravo Luigi, così e dai.
<font color="#00ffff"><i>Good Luigi, go on.</i></font>

978
01:05:29,778 --> 01:05:31,034
Devi essere più rapido.
<font color="#00ffff"><i>Be more faster.</i></font>

979
01:05:31,178 --> 01:05:33,897
Come on, now, boy!
It's a fight to the death!

980
01:05:35,443 --> 01:05:37,494
You either hit him or are you ain't?

981
01:05:41,907 --> 01:05:43,256
Ecco I con la spola tappeto.
<font color="#00ffff"><i>Make the carpet shuttle.</i></font>

982
01:05:43,346 --> 01:05:44,724
La spola tappeto giù!
<font color="#00ffff"><i>The carpet down!</i></font>

983
01:05:45,506 --> 01:05:47,303
Big Fred, come on!

984
01:05:48,487 --> 01:05:50,171
Turn him around!
Now...

985
01:05:53,826 --> 01:05:55,600
Use your strength, boy!

986
01:05:56,167 --> 01:05:58,164
Come on, now! Use your strength!

987
01:06:00,249 --> 01:06:01,303
There you go!

988
01:06:03,377 --> 01:06:04,480
There you go!

989
01:06:04,840 --> 01:06:05,931
Look at that.

990
01:06:06,995 --> 01:06:09,104
See, I told you to put
some more power in there.

991
01:06:09,848 --> 01:06:11,640
Do what I told you, boy!

992
01:06:12,347 --> 01:06:13,433
There you go!

993
01:06:13,973 --> 01:06:16,267
No!
Do what I told ya!

994
01:06:16,349 --> 01:06:19,393
Blind him black, boy!
Blind him black!

995
01:06:21,729 --> 01:06:23,401
Oh, no, Luigi.

996
01:06:43,793 --> 01:06:44,953
Finish him.

997
01:06:49,686 --> 01:06:50,943
Go on, boy, finish him!

998
01:06:55,887 --> 01:06:57,597
That's why they call him Big Fred.

999
01:06:57,678 --> 01:06:59,322
Worth every penny.

1000
01:06:59,323 --> 01:07:01,098
Well, arrivederci, Luigi.

1001
01:07:01,390 --> 01:07:03,658
Come on up, now, boy.
Get yourself a rest.

1002
01:07:03,759 --> 01:07:06,226
You did a fine job.
A real fine job.

1003
01:07:07,108 --> 01:07:08,107
Mercedes.

1004
01:07:29,922 --> 01:07:30,851
Tequila.

1005
01:07:41,142 --> 01:07:42,267
What's your name?

1006
01:07:44,967 --> 01:07:45,851
Django.

1007
01:07:48,803 --> 01:07:49,841
Can you spell it?

1008
01:07:52,660 --> 01:07:54,631
D-J-A-N

1009
01:07:55,012 --> 01:07:55,613
G

1010
01:07:56,018 --> 01:07:56,677
O

1011
01:07:58,256 --> 01:07:59,489
The D is silent.

1012
01:08:00,252 --> 01:08:01,002
I know.

1013
01:08:08,449 --> 01:08:09,481
Umberto, andiamo.
<font color="#00ffff"><i>Umberto, let's go.</i></font>

1014
01:08:09,590 --> 01:08:10,375
Mr. Moguy,

1015
01:08:10,953 --> 01:08:12,875
want you to take care
of my new boy here.

1016
01:08:13,083 --> 01:08:15,005
You find him a room with a soft bed,

1017
01:08:15,007 --> 01:08:17,258
then you bring him up a pony to lick his pole.

1018
01:08:17,764 --> 01:08:20,618
But you be ready to travel to Candyland
tomorrow morning, now, ya hear?

1019
01:08:20,679 --> 01:08:21,680
Yessir, Monsieur Candie.

1020
01:08:21,862 --> 01:08:23,218
Before you go Roscoe,

1021
01:08:23,328 --> 01:08:25,342
get Fred here a tall beer.

1022
01:08:29,615 --> 01:08:30,791
You enjoy that, boy.

1023
01:08:31,482 --> 01:08:32,401
You've earned it.

1024
01:08:32,770 --> 01:08:33,581
Yes sir.

1025
01:08:43,370 --> 01:08:44,560
What's your name, boy?

1026
01:08:44,970 --> 01:08:47,166
His name is Django Freeman.

1027
01:08:50,939 --> 01:08:52,181
Where'd you dig him up?

1028
01:08:52,270 --> 01:08:55,653
A fortuitous turn of events
brought Django and myself together.

1029
01:08:57,616 --> 01:08:59,101
I've heard tell about you.

1030
01:09:00,374 --> 01:09:03,468
I heard you been telling everybody
them Mandingos ain't no damn good.

1031
01:09:03,470 --> 01:09:06,418
Ain't nothing nobody is selling
is worth buying. I'm curious...

1032
01:09:07,379 --> 01:09:09,454
what makes you such
a Mandingo expert?

1033
01:09:11,783 --> 01:09:13,941
I'm curious what makes you so curious.

1034
01:09:17,537 --> 01:09:19,431
What did you say, boy?
Calm down, Butch.

1035
01:09:20,743 --> 01:09:21,966
No offense given...

1036
01:09:22,701 --> 01:09:23,734
none taken.

1037
01:09:24,078 --> 01:09:25,128
Monsieur Candie...

1038
01:09:26,136 --> 01:09:29,485
I'd appreciate if you could
direct your line of inquiry toward me.

1039
01:09:29,625 --> 01:09:30,442
One...

1040
01:09:31,710 --> 01:09:34,839
you do not have anything to drink.
Can I get you a tasty refreshment?

1041
01:09:35,005 --> 01:09:35,883
Yes!

1042
01:09:36,154 --> 01:09:37,842
I'll have a beer. Wunderbar.

1043
01:09:38,107 --> 01:09:40,302
Roscoe, a beer for the man
with the beard,

1044
01:09:40,304 --> 01:09:42,263
and I will have a Polynesian Pearl Diver.

1045
01:09:42,265 --> 01:09:43,586
Do not spare the rum.

1046
01:09:44,140 --> 01:09:45,011
Doc.

1047
01:09:46,381 --> 01:09:47,821
I am a seasoned slaver.

1048
01:09:48,008 --> 01:09:48,765
You are well,

1049
01:09:48,893 --> 01:09:50,023
you are a neophyte.

1050
01:09:50,025 --> 01:09:52,696
I'm simply trying to ascertain
if this cowboy here,

1051
01:09:52,758 --> 01:09:54,706
is taking advantage of you.

1052
01:09:56,402 --> 01:09:57,962
With all due respect,

1053
01:09:58,536 --> 01:09:59,410
Monsieur Candie...

1054
01:10:00,337 --> 01:10:02,214
I didn't seek you out for your advice.

1055
01:10:02,436 --> 01:10:04,823
I sought you out to purchase
a fighting nigger

1056
01:10:04,825 --> 01:10:06,749
at above top-dollar market price.

1057
01:10:07,371 --> 01:10:10,236
Now I was under the impression,
when you granted me an audience,

1058
01:10:10,238 --> 01:10:12,240
it would be to discuss business.

1059
01:10:15,456 --> 01:10:17,053
Well, we weren't talking business yet.

1060
01:10:17,884 --> 01:10:19,607
We were discussing my curiosity.

1061
01:10:22,428 --> 01:10:23,287
Thank you.

1062
01:10:23,596 --> 01:10:24,398
Roscoe,

1063
01:10:24,515 --> 01:10:26,034
Coco, go outside and play.

1064
01:10:28,309 --> 01:10:29,294
Sheba...

1065
01:10:29,880 --> 01:10:31,145
you stay right there.

1066
01:10:31,937 --> 01:10:33,480
I know you didn't mean me.

1067
01:10:35,416 --> 01:10:36,255
Prost!

1068
01:10:36,827 --> 01:10:37,635
German.

1069
01:10:38,780 --> 01:10:40,065
